[http://download.level1.tw/level1/manual/WBR-2400TX(EN).pdf Manual] "MADE IN TAIWAN" and "4900K301B" is silkscreened on the LED board in the FCC photos. The FCC test report specifies the CPU as the TNETW5305 ('''ARM7''') and the Flash and RAM size as 1MB and 4MB respectively (with ''Can Expand'' noted after the values). It also specifies the Switch chip as a Atan 8995L / AT8985P or '''Marvell''' 88E6052.. but the FCC image shows the device with an '''ADMtek''' Switch. This device uses the same board as the [[SerComm IP706ST]] (minus some minor changes like modularization of the LEDs). The default SSID may be '''default'''.
